    <div class="hero">
        <h2>Transforming Lives Through the Arts</h2>
        <p>Join us in creating equitable opportunities for all students.</p>
    </div>

    <section id="why">
        <h2>Why Arts Education Matters</h2>
        <p>Arts education fosters creativity, critical thinking, and emotional intelligence. Students engaged in the arts demonstrate better academic performance, social skills, and self-esteem. Yet, access to quality arts education remains inequitable, particularly for underserved communities. Join us in advocating for change.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="barriers">
        <h2>Understanding the Barriers</h2>
        <p>Many schools face funding cuts, policy challenges, and lack of awareness about the benefits of arts education. These barriers disproportionately affect low-income and minority students, perpetuating educational inequities.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="research">
        <h2>Our Research & Advocacy</h2>
        <p>Our research highlights the profound benefits of arts education and the systemic barriers that hinder access. We propose sustainable solutions, including advocacy for policy changes, community engagement, and partnerships to bridge the gap.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="action">
